While DNA results have confirmed that the human remains found in the sewer pipes on the property of murder accused Daniel Smit, belongs to Jerobejin van Wyk, 13, police are searching for another missing boy. Anelisa Lathitha Sigwebedlana, 11, was reported as missing on Wednesday,  by his mother Zanele Sigwebedlana. The boy was last seen by his aunt at home in Riemvasmaak informal settlement Tuesday at about 4pm. He was last seen dressed in a yellow long sleeve T-shirt and a grey short. According to provincial police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk, a Joint Operations Centre (JOC) was established to monitor the situation. “SAPS, the community policing forum, neighbourhood watch, residents, executive mayor and councillors and the K9 Dog Unit were all involved in the search for the boy. Two weeks ago Jerobejin van Wyk’s disappearance sparked an outcry in the small town. Two days after his disappearance, train driver Daniel Smit, 56, was arrested after police found human remains to believed to be Jerobejin’s on his property. According to witnesses on the scene, the remains found in the sewer pipes consisted of a lung, ear and skin.  Anyone with any information on his whereabouts can contact the investigating officer Detective Warrant Officer Maarman from FCS, Vredendal on 082 334 8931 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.